The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, June 6 (PTI): Air India today said it had disbursed Rs 11.29 crore as interim compensation among the families of 129 victims and some survivors of the Mangalore plane crash.          
	Besides, Rs 1.47 crore has been disbursed from the Prime Ministers Relief Fund, an Air India spokesperson said. Air India had announced an interim compensation of Rs 10 lakh for the families of the dead who were above 12 years of age and Rs 5 lakh for the families of the rest of the dead. The airline had promised Rs 2 lakh to each injured.                  
	 Ballia, UP (PTI): A Dalit youth was beaten to death on Saturday after he attended a wedding, defying a village diktat, police said. However, some people have lodged a complaint alleging that the attack came in retaliation to the rape of a 15-year-old girl by the youth.                  
	 Burdwan: A Trinamul Congress supporter died in Burdwans Ketugram on Sunday afternoon when crude bombs he was carrying in a bucket exploded. Sheikh Ripon, 24, was allegedly taking the bombs to a CPM stronghold where supporters of the two parties were locked in a clash. In neighbouring Hooghly district, over 80 Trinamul activists last night damaged over a dozen thatched houses of CPM supporters and set three of them ablaze. Samoshpur village, where the attack took place, is on the outskirts of the Tarakeswar municipal area, where the Opposition won the recent civic polls for the first time in four decades.                  
	 Gorakhpur (PTI): BJP MP Yogi Adityanath has been named as one of the targets in a threat letter sent allegedly by the Jaish-e-Mohammad. The letter, addressed to the Uttar Pradesh director-general of police, was received on Friday. It had been sent through speed post by a certain Mujahideen Siddiqui, who identified himself as a Jaish member .                  
	Balaghat, MP (PTI): Two persons were arrested on Saturday for killing a cheetal at the Khursodi jungle near Balaghat, police said. However, five others managed to flee.                                                                                                                                              
